<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SAN CLEMENTE; 
</P>
<P>
POLICE RAID 2 HOMES AND ARREST 5 PEOPLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WENDY PAULSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A team of 20 police officers raided two homes over the weekend, arresting five 
people on a variety of charges, including possession of cocaine for sale and 
possession of stolen property, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The raids, which began at 8:15 p.m. Friday, were in a north San Clemente 
neighborhood that police said has been the scene of several disturbances over 
the past few weeks. 
</P>
<P>
"A team of 20 officers served a search warrant on an apartment . . . where 
undercover officers had bought cocaine and marijuana while doing an 
investigation of criminal activity in the neighborhood," Sgt. Richard E. 
Downing said. 
</P>
<P>
Arrested for possession of half an ounce of cocaine was Mario Hurtato, 25, who 
lives at the apartment in the 100 block of West Escalones. Also arrested at the 
scene for outstanding misdemeanor warrants were Lorenzo Hurtato, 20, and 
Francisco Cazares, 30, Downing said. 
</P>
<P>
One hour later, police went to a home on the 800 block of Calle Puente, behind 
West Escalones, and arrested two men on suspicion of having stolen property, 
believed to have been taken from a local dentist's office two weeks earlier, 
Downing said. Joel Gonzales, 18, and Juan Nejorado, 20, both of San Clemente, 
remain in custody. 
</P>
<P>
Councilman Brian J. Rice said the arrests indicate the city's proactive stance 
on stomping out minor criminal activities before they escalate. 
</P>
<P>
"Sending 20 officers out there makes a statement that the city is going to 
accentuate that area," Rice said. "We have not had anything of a tremendous 
concern happen, but the same problems keep cropping up in the same area, so the 
city is coming from a very proactive angle to prevent things from getting out 
of hand." WENDY PAULSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
