<P>
MAN ARRESTED IN THREATS WITH PISTOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AARON CURTISS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Fillmore man was arrested Sunday after he threatened two brothers with a 
handgun during an argument over a girlfriend, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Leo Medina, 21, was taken into custody about 4:45 p.m. outside his home in the 
300 block of B Street, Ventura County Sheriff's Lt. Kathy Kemp said. 
</P>
<P>
Kemp said Medina began arguing with Steve Segovia, 26, of Fillmore over a 
former girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
The argument became heated and Medina brandished a 9-millimeter semiautomatic 
handgun, Kemp said, adding that he threatened to shoot Segovia and his brother, 
Jessie, 26. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies arrived before any shots were fired. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured. AARON CURTISS 
