<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FIRE BURNS 20 ACRES IN SANTA CLARITA VALLEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A fire suspected to be arson blackened about 20 acres of brush in the Santa 
Clarita Valley Sunday, but firefighters contained the blaze before it reached 
several nearby homes, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injuries and no residents were evacuated. 
</P>
<P>
Two teen-agers were detained by sheriff's deputies shortly after the fire near 
San Fernando Road and Valle del Oro was reported at about 4:45 p.m., said 
Assistant Chief Leon Provost of the Los Angeles County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
A 17-year-old from North Hollywood and a 15-year-old from Lancaster were 
released to the custody of their parents, said Los Angeles County Sheriff Sgt. 
Michael Watner. 
</P>
<P>
Provost said the teen-agers, whose names were not released because of their 
age, were seen leaving the site where the fire broke out behind Shady Mobile 
Home Park. 
</P>
<P>
Several large houses in Placerita Canyon were threatened by the flames, but 
about 235 firefighters had contained the fire by 6 p.m. Provost said about 100 
firefighters would remain until late Sunday night to extinguish hot spots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
