<HEADLINE>
<P>
S.D. OFFICER UNHURT IN SHOOTING INCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Passengers in a pickup truck fired at least five shots from a small caliber 
weapon at a police supervisor in an unmarked police car early Sunday at Chicano 
Park in South San Diego, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Two or three people in a Nissan pickup truck fired at the officer, who was in 
the park to investigate an earlier shooting, Sgt. Fred England said. Neither 
the officer nor his passenger, a dispatcher, were injured in the gunfire that 
occurred at 3:47 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
The pickup truck was later found at 17th and J streets, its interior burned, 
England said. Police are still investigating. 
</P>
<P>
"It's unusual to have an undercover unit shot at," England said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
