<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIDERS; 
</P>
<P>
LONG REPORTS TO CAMP, SAYS HE HAD PERSONAL BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS BAKER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OXNARD 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saying it was just a case of miscommunication, Howie Long reported to the 
Raiders' training camp late Saturday night after a one-day unexcused absence. 
</P>
<P>
Why did Long fail to report to training camp on Friday, the first day veterans 
were due? 
</P>
<P>
"Not to be sarcastic, but it's personal," Long said. "I just had to take care 
of some family business. It was just a case of something popping up at the last 
minute, and I had no choice." 
</P>
<P>
Why didn't Long inform Coach Art Shell of his absence? 
</P>
<P>
"I didn't speak to Art, but I spoke to management and everything was fine," 
Long said. 
</P>
<P>
But Shell apparently never got the message. 
</P>
<P>
Shell said everything was fine. 
</P>
<P>
"I met with him and I was satisfied with everything he had to say," Shell said. 
"This chapter is closed." 
</P>
<P>
While the case is closed on Long, who practiced for the first time Sunday, the 
cases remain open for the Raiders' eight holdouts: quarterback Steve Beuerlein, 
tailback Marcus Allen, fullback Steve Smith, cornerback Mike Haynes, safety 
Vann McElroy, tight end Mike Dyal, defensive end Greg Townsend and defensive 
end Anthony Smith, their No. 1 draft pick. 
</P>
<P>
Has there been any progress in negotiations? 
</P>
<P>
"I'm just waiting for them to tell me when they're coming in," Shell said. 
</P>
<P>
Raider Notes 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders released safety Russell Carter, a seven-year veteran. "We're going 
in a different direction and we feel comfortable with the younger players we 
have," Coach Art Shell said. "We released him early to give him an opportunity 
to catch on with someone else." . . . The Raiders also cut Anthony Grove, a 
rookie wide receiver from LaVerne. . . . Defensive end Lyle Alzado, attempting 
to make a comeback at 41, didn't practice Sunday. Shell said that Alzado had 
suffered a strained calf muscle. Alzado's status is listed as day to day. . . . 
Linebacker Bruce Klosterman sat out Sunday's practice because of a hamstring 
injury, and running back Leon Perry was sidelined because of a shoulder injury. 
</P>
