<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE KILLS FATHER, 2 YOUNG SONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A father and his two young sons died in a fast-moving fire in their Long Beach 
apartment despite rescue attempts that were thwarted by a wrought-iron gate 
blocking the front door, officials said this morning. 
</P>
<P>
Two reserve police officers saw smoke coming from the apartment building on 
East 11th St. at 8:11 p.m. Sunday and tried unsuccessfully to enter the 
apartment, said Long Beach Fire Department Lt. Doug Sarvis. Firefighters 
arrived minutes later and broke into the apartment, pulling the three victims 
from the flaming unit, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Curtis Lyles, 29, and Jamal Lyles, 4, died at the scene. Another son, Curtis 
Lyles Jr., 7, died at St. Mary Medical Center. The fire was believed to be 
accidental. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
