<P>
BARR HUBBY TATTLED TO ENQUIRER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Where does the National Enquirer get all those wild stories about Roseanne 
Barr? Some of them came from an unlikely paid informant -- Barr's husband, Tom 
Arnold, according to one of the tabloid's reporters. 
</P>
<P>
In an interview on "Geraldo" that will air Wednesday, reporter Brian Williams 
said, "Tom was eager to, shall we say, earn a little extra money in his own 
right so he helped us on a number of stories. 
</P>
<P>
In particular, before they were getting married, he, in a macho way, wanted to 
pay for his own honeymoon. Of course, Roseanne makes millions and millions of 
dollars and Tom was barely surviving as a stand-up comedian. So he sold us a 
series of stories in the hope of being able to pay for their honeymoon." 
</P>
<P>
Enquirer General Editor Steve Coz described Barr as a tabloid journalist's 
dream. "She's crazy and everyone around her is crazy and they love to talk to 
tabloids," he said. "So you just get story after story about her." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Tom Arnold 
</P>
