<P>
STALLONE WANTS MORE DIALOGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Sylvester Stallone says he will flex his brain more than his biceps in 
films. 
</P>
<P>
Stallone, 44, who rose to prominence with the original "Rocky" film about an 
underdog fighter, said in this week's People magazine that audiences cannot 
identify with the kind of super-hero he portrayed in "Rambo III." 
</P>
<P>
"I recently saw 'Rambo III' again and recoiled at a scene where, strong and 
invulnerable, I stood up there. I mean, I was so invincible, I had veins in my 
hair. There I was, superhuman, with my gun obliterating everyone crossing my 
path," Stallone said. 
</P>
<P>
He said filmmakers need to place more emphasis on developing characters. 
</P>
<P>
"Right now, we don't care about dialogue. We know it's just a boring interlude 
before the action starts." 
</P>
</TEXT>
