<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE'S PHARMACY: ONIONS, IF NOT TOBACCO, CAN RELIEVE PAIN OF BEE STINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOE GRAEDON and TERESA GRAEDON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: At our family reunion last week my little niece was stung by a yellow 
jacket. My dad said his father always swore by tobacco juice, but no one at the 
gathering was chewing tobacco. Someone tried soaking a cigarette and squeezing 
the juice on the sting, but that didn't work. 
</P>
<P>
Isn't there some other home remedy that would work to take away the pain of a 
sting? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: In our part of the country tobacco juice is an old home remedy for bee 
stings too, but we've never seen any scientific data to show if this works. 
</P>
<P>
But one of our readers came up with a home remedy for stings that really took 
our breath away. He credits his German neighbor lady with suggesting that a cut 
onion be applied to the sting for at least 10 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
When we checked with the world-renowned onion researcher, Dr. Eric Block of the 
State University of New York at Albany, he confirmed that a fresh-cut onion may 
minimize the pain. Onions contain an ingredient that can break down the 
chemicals responsible for inflammation and discomfort. 
</P>
<P>
Q: I will be attending my 25th class reunion next month and I am feeling 
embarrassed about my weight. I weigh 12 pounds more now than I did at the last 
reunion, and my classmates made fun of me then. 
</P>
<P>
I came across a diet pill that promised I could lose up to five pounds a week. 
The ingredient is guar gum. What is it and how does it work? 
</P>
<P>
A: Guar gum is a soluble fiber from guar seeds. Like the fiber in oat bran and 
pectin, guar gum has been shown to lower cholesterol and perhaps even improve 
blood sugar levels in diabetics. 
</P>
<P>
There is controversy, however, about whether guar gum actually promotes weight 
loss. Although you might have a feeling of fullness after consuming this fiber, 
you should not expect to lose a lot of weight in a short period of time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
